args:
The prince arrives at the heart of the enemy's
hold and learns their true goal: the release of a
terrible demon imprisoned in the sealing stone.
The head priest then absorbs the demon's
power, manifesting as a dark version of Ramiel.
He's quite the talent, our Nevin.\nA shame he doesn't apply himself more.
Can you drop the disappointed dad shtick,\nplease? One per day is plenty.
Shh! I see shadows moving ahead.
Let's go spread this miasma around\nbefore I go wroth outta boredom!
I'd be leadin' the way if he was here,\nbut ya know we can't just walk outta\nhere with the sealin' stone.
Not unless you wish to face\nmost terrible consequences.
Gya! H-hey, so I was just kiddin', yeah?!\nI wasn't never gonna leave!
And I ain't fool enough to drive m'self mad\ncause we ain't got that special ore'a yours.
But now that ya ARE here,\nI take it we're headin' out?
Yes. This will be the final time.
Still standing after that, are we?\nYou're tougher than you look.
Who'n the sweet crap are YOU?!
I did not expect to be found so easily.\nPerhaps I did not give the northern Church\nand this traitorous prince enough credit.
If you know of us, you know what we are\ncapable of. Return what you have stolen\nand no blood need be shed this day.
Stolen? Ah, you mean the sealing stone?
We know you're using that stone\nto create the wroth phenomenon!
Why would a priest of the Ilian Church\ndeign do such a thing?!
Do you truly not know? Have you actually\ncome all this way on blind faith alone?
Perhaps I should not be surprised;\nthe stone is a closely guarded secret\neven among the Church's inner circle.
Then how, exactly, did a rank-and-file\ngrunt of your ilk come to know of it?
I was CHOSEN, you foul-tongued angel!\nI am different from the rest!
Yes! I am chosen in the same way\nas those apostles by your side!
In what world are you and I alike?
Oh, he's told me all about your kind—\nand about how apostles will stoop to any\nmeans to see their brand of justice done.

The old me was hobbled by fear of failure.
Too cowardly to get my hands dirty,
I instead clasped them in endless,
futile prayer to the Goddess.

But those prayers achieved nothing,
for only those willing to stain their hands
will ever grasp success! Only through
action can we usher in true change!
We are called to guide our flock through\naction—HE has taught me this!

Great sermon, super inspiring. There's just
one problem: what you're doing is evil.
Spilling blood and sowing chaos is a far
cry from our work in the Goddess's name.

Good and evil are subjective nonsense,
and I will gladly sully my hands to see our
noble goals achieved. I will serve as a
necessary evil to this end!
Hey, maybe you can stop foaming at the\nmouth for a second and tell us what you're\nactually PLANNING here?
I mean to release what dwells within the\nsealing stone. The demon must awaken!
Demon? What are you talking about?

I speak of the demon sealed inside the
stone by the Church untold ages ago—
the secret they have tried so desperately
to keep from the world!
But soon the seal will break! The stone has\ndrunk deep of the miasma shrouding this\nregion, and its hold wavers as we speak!
As I suspected: You've driven man and\nbeast alike mad just to flood the area\nwith miasma and weaken the seal.
The demon? The nature of the stone?\nSurely you knew of this from the start,\neven as a lesser archangel.

And yet you've told your henchmen here
naught of it. Is this an attempt to preserve
the Church's good name, or do you simply
not trust them with the information?
I have not come for conversation, and will\nwaste neither time nor breath on you.
My purpose is to retrieve that stone before\na sad fool looses an evil beyond his ken\non the entire world.
And you will fail! Your arrival changes\nnothing save the timing, for these\nsacrificial lambs are plenty!
What?! Hey, hold on just a second there!\nWithout them stones, the miasma'll...\nGRAAAAGH!
Aaaah ha ha! Wonderful... WONDERFUL!\nI can feel its power surging!
Everyone, get clear of here at once!
Uh, but don't we need to take that\nstone thingie back from the priest?
That was the plan, but we are too late—\nthe demon is stirring.
Is that not all the more reason\nto stand and fight?
The power it possesses is immeasurable,\nand we cannot stand against it. We must\nfall back and find the other apostles!
And you think I would permit your escape?
They're so coordinated... I can scarce\nbelieve they've lost their conscious minds!
I'll deal with this. The rest of you, run!
Did you hear me, Pinon?\nGet out of here now!
I won't leave you to do this alone!\nI am an apostle, the same as you!
I told you I would lighten your load,\nand you said you would count on me\nto do so, remember?
Well, yeah, but THIS isn't exactly what\nI had in mind when—
If not now, when?! There will not BE\na next time if we fail here!
What window we had to run has closed.\nOnly one path now remains...
Sweet moldy gravy... The hell is THAT?!
I am born anew through the demon's\npower! I have become his vessel to wreak\nchaos unto all! Witness me! WITNESS ME!
Wait, why does he look just like...?
...Like me! Is this a version of myself\ncome forth from another world?
We may share a visage, but let us see\nif you power is my equal! HAAAAAH!
Is this a demon's strength?\nIt is overwhelming!
You glimpse but a fraction! Even now,\npower continues to flow into me through\nthe stone! Aaaaah ha ha ha ha!
Whatever your goals, they can't be worth\naccepting this kind of unholy power!
I serve as a necessary evil, and will bring\nthe shadow of chaos to every corner of this\nsad and blighted world.
Whatever your faults, you were a priest of\nIlia's word. To speak now of plunging Her\nflock into chaos is madness itself!
This WORLD is madness! North and south\nwield their own selfish view of right as a\ncudgel against the other in endless war!
I aim to create a world without conflict;\na world where all hearts are united.
Your actions could not be leading you\nfurther from that goal, cur!

Oh, but they will—I am certain of it.
Once a demon emerges to threaten all
existence, mankind will have no choice
but to unite against it.

And in that hour of crisis, I will once more
spread the word of the Goddess and drive
that threat from this world! Then all people
will accept ME as their savior!
Wait, so you're doing all this just so\nyou can be some kinda big-shot?!
A rotten plan well-suited to a demon.\nToo bad the gospel of Ilia isn't some tool\nto fulfill your sad need for acceptance.
This is blasphemy, and as an apostle\nof the Goddess, I will not allow it!
My apologies, but I must ask your help\na while longer, {player_name}.
Come, then! Kneel before my iron will!
